"https://cloudfront-us-east-2.images.arcpublishing.com/reuters/KDCG34ZGPNNSTO7YZK37TDNESY.jpg","caption":"Sri Lanka Navy personnel assist Iranian sailors during a rescue operation after responding to a distress call from their vessel, the Iranian military ship, IRIS Dena, within Sri Lanka’s maritime search and rescue region, in the Indian Ocean, March 4.  via Sri Lanka Navy","type":"image","resizer_url":"https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/KDCG34ZGPNNSTO7YZK37TDNESY.jpg?auth=817af32d6d37d53d0ef91f32016ab7cf56f6e89a92a75f6545211c06f3cf789d","location":"INDIAN OCEAN, Sri Lanka","id":"KDCG34ZGPNNSTO7YZK37TDNESY","authors":"SRI LANKAN NAVY","alt_text":"Sri Lanka Navy personnel assist Iranian sailors during a rescue operation in Indian Ocean","width":977,"height":609,"subtitle":"Sri Lanka Navy personnel assist Iranian sailors during a rescue operation in Indian Ocean","slug":"IRAN-CRISIS-SHIP-SRI-LANKA","updated_at":"2026-03-06T22:14:42Z","company":"Reuters","purchase_licensing_path":"https://www.reutersconnect.com/item/sri-lanka-navy-personnel-assist-iranian-sailors-during-a-rescue-operation-in-indian-ocean/dGFnOnJldXRlcnMuY29tLDIwMjY6bmV3c21sX1JDMk1YSkFPM003Qg%3D%3D/?utm_medium=rcom-article-media&utm_campaign=rcom-rcp-lead"},"authors":[{"id":"humeyra.pamuk@thomsonreuters.com","name":"Humeyra Pamuk","first_name":"Humeyra","last_name":"Pamuk","company":"Reuters","thumbnail":{"url":"https://author-service-images-prod-us-east-1.publishing.aws.arc.pub/reuters/aa22fc83-e232-4f6f-bcdb-7021abebd052.png","type":"image","resizer_url":"https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/https%3A%2F%2Fauthor-service-images-prod-us-east-1.publishing.aws.arc.pub%2Freuters%2Faa22fc83-e232-4f6f-bcdb-7021abebd052.png?auth=a651d7df620bad8876f9827933a543c1dce067cba93a5706e5a2c8bfbc20b9b4"},"social_links":[{"site":"email","url":"mailto:humeyra.pamuk@thomsonreuters.com"},{"site":"twitter","url":"https://x.com/humeyra_pamuk"},{"site":"instagram","url":"https://www.instagram.com/humeyra_reuters/"},{"site":"linkedin","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/humeyra-pamuk-1b971127/"}],"byline":"Humeyra Pamuk","description":"Humeyra Pamuk is a senior foreign policy correspondent based in Washington DC. She covers the U.S. State Department, regularly traveling with U.S. Secretary of State. During her 20 years with Reuters, she has had postings in London, Dubai, Cairo and Turkey, covering everything from the Arab Spring and Syria's civil war to numerous Turkish elections and the Kurdish insurgency in the southeast. In 2017, she won the Knight-Bagehot fellowship program at Columbia University’s School of Journalism. She holds a BA in International Relations and an MA on European Union studies.","topic_url":"/authors/humeyra-pamuk/","role":"Senior Foreign Policy Correspondent"}],"display_time":"2026-03-06T18:11:10.059Z"},{"id":"BK7BMT4P6JOYNPEV5SJPWI5SIY","revision_id":"XGUGV3PN5NEOBDFCNDYSZRRJSU","canonical_url":"/world/middle-east/us-state-department-approves-possible-military-sale-israel-1518-million-2026-03-07/","website":"reuters","web":"US skips congressional review to approve munitions sale to Israel","native":"US skips congressional review to approve munitions sale to Israel","published":true,"updated_time":"2026-03-07T02:01:25.890Z","published_time":"2026-03-07T01:49:31.528Z","article_type":"Standard","display_my_news":true,"display_newsletter_signup":true,"display_notifications":true,"display_related_media":true,"display_related_organizations":true,"content_code":"metered","source":{"name":"Reuters","original_name":"Reuters"},"title":"US skips congressional review to approve munitions sale to Israel","basic_headline":"US skips congressional review to approve munitions sale to Israel","distributor":"Reuters","description":"The U.S. State Department ​said on Friday ‌it has made a determination approving a ​possible foreign military ​sale to Israel of ⁠munitions and munitions ​support for $151.8 million, without congressional ​review.","primary_media_type":"image","primary_ta